Preconditions:
- The input grid is a 2D array of integers.
- The grid has at least one row and one column.
- Each element in the grid is either 0 or 1.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the number of elements in the largest square subgrid that has all 1s on its border.
- If there is no such subgrid in the grid, the method returns 0.